  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-DOC-03, restructure `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`: max-width **960 px** (verify current 85vw and adjust). Body becomes a **2-column grid**: left ~640 px thumbnail area; right 320 px metadata pane with sections (top→bottom) — **AI summary** (sparkle icon + paragraph), **Tags** (single chip from `sprk_documenttype` value), **Details** (Created by / Created / Size / Type). Footer actions left-to-right: **Find similar** (subtle) · **Close** (secondary) · **Open file** (primary). The dialog header 3-dot menu was wired in task 040 (FR-DOC-01); do NOT change the menu. Existing iframe preview load behavior unchanged.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer with Fluent UI v9 `Dialog` + layout-grid expertise. Familiar with `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, the iframe preview pipeline, and the sparkle/AI summary affordance from `AiSummaryPopover.tsx`.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` renders at 960 px max-width on viewports ≥1024 px. Body uses a 2-column CSS grid (640 px / 320 px) with the metadata pane sections in the specified order. Footer buttons reordered with correct appearances. Existing iframe preview pipeline unchanged. PCF builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DOC-03 modernizes the dialog layout: today it is a single-column ~85vw dialog with the iframe taking the full width and metadata stacked above/below. The new layout puts the iframe on the left and a structured metadata pane on the right. Task 040 already replaced the dialog-toolbar icons with the 3-dot menu — this task focuses purely on body + footer layout. The dialog's iframe preview pipeline (SPE preview URL generation, content rendering) is untouched.
    </background>
