    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Dialog sizing" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md">
        Dialog `surface` slot accepts inline style for max-width; ensure portal-rendered Dialog respects size at MDA viewport.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="2-column grid via makeStyles" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md">
        Use `display: grid; gridTemplateColumns: '640px 320px'` with token-based gap; collapse below 1024 px (not required for v1).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">Verify context &lt; 60%. If higher, run `context-handoff` before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="0.5" name="Invoke fluent-v9-component">Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` (binding per design.md §6.0). Load `fluent-v9-component-authoring.md`, `fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md`, `fluent-v9-theming.md`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Load knowledge">Read ADR-006, ADR-021, ADR-022, ADR-028; PCF CLAUDE.md. Read existing `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` — note the current 85vw size, the iframe rendering, and the metadata layout. Read `AiSummaryPopover.tsx` to understand how AI summary content is fetched/rendered.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Set dialog max-width to 960 px">In `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, change the `DialogSurface` (or equivalent) max-width style to `960px`. Verify Fluent v9 Dialog respects the size at viewport ≥1024 px.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement 2-column body grid">Replace the body layout with a CSS grid: `display: grid; gridTemplateColumns: '640px 320px'; gap: tokens.spacingHorizontalL`. Left cell: iframe thumbnail area (existing iframe logic preserved). Right cell: metadata pane.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Build AI summary section">In the right cell, add the first section: sparkle icon + heading "AI summary" + paragraph containing the AI summary content (reuse the same data source as `AiSummaryPopover.tsx`). Render skeleton while loading.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Build Tags section">Add the second section: heading "Tags" + a single Fluent v9 `Tag` chip showing the document's `documentType` (label from option set, not raw value). If `documentType` is empty, render nothing (or a subtle dash).</step>
    <step order="6" name="Build Details section">Add the third section: heading "Details" + key-value list — Created by / Created / Size / Type. Use Fluent v9 `Text` with token-based typography. Format dates via existing date-formatting helper; format size in KB/MB.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Reorder footer buttons">Replace existing footer with three Fluent v9 `Button` controls in order: Find similar (`appearance="subtle"`) · Close (`appearance="secondary"`) · Open file (`appearance="primary"`). Wire to existing handlers in `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Preserve iframe preview pipeline">Verify the SPE preview URL fetch + iframe `src` binding is byte-identical to pre-change. The iframe element moves into the left grid cell but the data flow is unchanged.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Preserve 3-dot menu in header">Confirm task 040's `DocumentRowMenu` in the dialog header remains untouched.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Dark-mode + a11y check">Run PCF in dev harness with `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`. Verify all three sections + footer buttons render with v9 tokens. Run axe scan in both themes. Verify dialog max-width clamps at 960 px at viewports ≥1024 px (resize test).</step>
    <step order="11" name="Build verification">Run `npm run build:prod` from PCF root.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">Invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check`. Resolve all findings.</step>
    <step order="12" name="Checkpoint">Run `context-handoff` (silent: ✅ Checkpoint).</step>
    <step order="13" name="Update task tracking">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 044 status 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task (045).</step>
  </steps>

