  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Dialog renders at 960 px max-width on viewports ≥1024 px (verify via DOM inspect of DialogSurface).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Body uses 2-column grid: left ~640 px (iframe), right 320 px (metadata pane).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Metadata pane sections render in order: AI summary · Tags · Details (Created by / Created / Size / Type).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Footer buttons render in order Find similar (subtle) · Close (secondary) · Open file (primary).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing iframe preview pipeline unchanged — SPE preview URL fetch + iframe src binding byte-identical to pre-change.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Header 3-dot menu (from task 040) unchanged.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF builds clean; zero hardcoded hex/rgb.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">axe WCAG 2.1 AA zero violations in light AND dark.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` skills pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows task 044 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Dialog renders at 960 px on ≥1024 px viewport">
      <steps>
        <step>Open a result row to launch FilePreviewDialog at 1280 px viewport.</step>
        <step>DOM inspect: confirm DialogSurface max-width = 960 px.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Width clamped to 960 px regardless of viewport above 1024 px.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Metadata sections in correct order">
      <steps>
        <step>Open a doc with full metadata.</step>
        <step>Verify right pane top→bottom: AI summary heading + paragraph · Tags chip · Details (Created by / Created / Size / Type).</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Three sections in spec order.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Footer buttons appearance + order">
      <steps>
        <step>Verify footer left→right: Find similar (subtle) · Close (secondary) · Open file (primary).</step>
        <step>Click each button — verify handler fires correctly (Find similar triggers find-similar flow; Close dismisses; Open file opens SPE file).</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Order + appearances + handlers correct.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="iframe preview unchanged">
      <steps>
        <step>Open a doc — verify iframe loads SPE preview URL identically to pre-change behavior.</step>
        <step>Network tab: verify SPE preview URL request is unchanged.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Preview pipeline byte-identical.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark mode compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode; open the dialog.</step>
        <step>Verify all three sections, footer buttons, and dialog surface use v9 dark tokens.</step>
        <step>Run axe-core in both themes.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Zero WCAG violations; all tokens.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Depends on task 040 (3-dot menu in dialog header already replaced toolbar icons). The iframe preview pipeline is OUT OF SCOPE — do not touch SPE preview URL generation. AI summary section uses the same data source as `AiSummaryPopover.tsx` — do NOT duplicate fetch logic; consider extracting to a hook (`useAiSummary(documentId)`) if cleaner. Single Tag chip from `documentType` — multi-tag is not in spec (only the document's primary type).
  </notes>

